The paper discusses the regularization effects of variational distributions on learning in generative models, specifically in the context of variational autoencoders (VAEs). This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new objective function for VAEs that unifies them with regularized autoencoders, which could also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
